}}<10^{-2}$. Models with $\\epsilon_{\\rm{DC}}\\sim1$ instead\nrequire a high mass threshold close to $M_{\\rm{h}}\\gtrsim10^{13}M_{\\odot}$. We\ninvestigate the impact of $\\epsilon_{\\rm{DC}}$ and $\\Sigma$ on measurements of\nclustering and find there is no luminosity dependence on clustering for\n$\\Sigma>0.3$, consistent with recent observations from Subaru HSC.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Apr 2020 01:12:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
