{"id":"2004.07479","submitter":"Denis Osin","authors":"D. Osin","title":"A topological zero-one law and elementary equivalence of finitely\n  generated groups","comments":"This version corrects some inaccuracies that appeared in previous\n  versions and the published version of the paper","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.GR math.LO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $\\mathcal G$ denote the space of finitely generated marked groups. We\ngive equivalent characterizations of closed subspaces $\\mathcal S\\subseteq\n\\mathcal G$ satisfying the following zero-one law: for any sentence $\\sigma$ in\nthe infinitary logic $\\mathcal L_{\\omega_1, \\omega}$, the set of all models of\n$\\sigma$ in $\\mathcal S$ is either meager or comeager. In particular, we show\nthat the zero-one law holds for certain natural spaces associated to hyperbolic\ngroups and their generalizations. As an application, we obtain that generic\ntorsion-free lacunary hyperbolic groups are elementarily equivalent; the same\nclaim holds for lacunary hyperbolic groups without non-trivial finite normal\nsubgroups. Our paper has a substantial expository component. We give\nstreamlined proofs of some known results and survey ideas from topology, logic,\nand geometric group theory relevant to our work. We also discuss some open\nproblems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Apr 2020 06:32:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 3 Aug 2020 20:16:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 20 Aug 2020 02:19:18 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 23 Oct 2020 19:18:50 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 20 Nov 2020 02:32:47 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Sat, 24 Sep 2022 02:00:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-27"}
